INFORMATION ‼️
‘Cag Kebab’ is yet another delicious kebab variety of Turkish cuisine. It is originated from the Erzurum city which locates at the heart of the Eastern Anatolia Region of Turkey. At first sight, Cag Kebab may look like a Döner Kebab to you; however, it is different in how it made and taste.

‘Cag Kebab’ is made with the combination of boneless lamb ribs and boneless leg of lamb meat. On the other hand, Döner Kebab is made with a combination of boneless veal meat, lamb meat, and tail fat. When it comes to cooking styles, Cag Kebab cooks at the wood fire on a horizontal rotisserie; however, Döner Kebab cooks at a specially designed electric vertical rotisserie.

Miguel of @cooking_with_fire___ fires up some cheesy chimichurri quesadillas on the @nomadgrills. Marinate with chimichurri sauce (Miguel's recipe below) then sear for 4 minutes per side. Let rest for 5 minutes before slicing. Add cheese to your tortilla and top with heaps of meat. Garnish with cilantro, red onion, lemon juice, creamy chipotle sauce and enjoy.

= Chimichurri =
• 1 bunch flat leaf parsley
• 2 tsp oregano
• 4 minced garlic cloves
• 1 tsp chili flakes
• 1/4 cup red wine vinegar
• 1/2 cup olive oil

• Salt & pepper to taste

= Creamy Chipotle Sauce =
• 3 tbsp sour cream
• 1 tbsp chipotle
• 1 tsp cilantro
• Juice of 1/2 a lemon
• Salt & pepper to taste

The king of outdoor cooking, Max of @grillhunters, takes on the king of seafood on his @nomadgrills — melted with some garlic, herbs and lemon compound butter. Max's tribe is stoked for the smell of some smoked lobster in the air! 🦞🦞 #nomadgrills

= INGREDIENTS =
• 2 Live Lobster

= COMPOUND BUTTER =
• ½ cup butter softened
• 2 tbsp lemon juice
• 2 cloves garlic minced
• 1½ tbsp fresh chives chopped
• 1½ tbsp fresh rosemary chopped
• 1½ tbsp lemon zest
• ½ tsp kosher salt
• ½ tsp pepper

= INSTRUCTIONS =
• Fire up coals in a chimney.
• While the coals are heating up, mix all the compound butter in a small bowl.
• In the center of a plastic wrap, put the compound butter and wrap tightly both ends.
• Place in the refrigerator while prepping the lobster.
• Slice both lobsters lengthwise, inserting the knife between both eyes first to neutralize nervous system.
• Place your hot coals under the cooking grates.
• Melt about 2 tbsp of the compound butter and pour on the raw lobster meat.
• Place the half lobsters, meat down, on the smoking grates.
• After 5 minutes, turn the lobsters over, place a cube of compound butter on top and cook for another 3 minutes.

For pitmaster @_howlowcanyouslow, low & slow on the @nomadgrills is the way to go when it comes to the taco. JP recommends reverse searing a steak (1-inch thick rib eye) to build up a firm crust. Follow the rest of these taco tips to tasty tendertown...

1.) Season (rub recipe below) and place steak on the indirect side and smoke to an internal temp of about 120ºF. Remove and let rest for 10 minutes (by resting first, you can serve as soon as it's done searing).

2.) Move your steak to the direct side and sear for about 2 minutes each side to lock in your juices and add an extra layer of texture and flavor.

3.) Slice into ½ inch pieces and serve on soft flour tortillas with your favorite ingredients (e.g., pickled jalapeños, avocado, Mexican crema, cotija cheese, lettuce, cilantro, red onion, lime juice, etc.).

= JP's All Black Rub Recipe =
• 2 tbsp kosher salt
• 2 tbsp cracked black pepper
• 1 tbsp garlic powder
• ½ tbsp food grade, activated charcoal

Homemade Birria Taco Recipe 🌮👌

INGREDIENTS 👨‍🍳:

4 lb beef cheeks 
4 dried ancho chiles
2 dried guajillo chiles
8 chile de arbol
1 tsp pepper
1 tsp dried thyme
3 bay leaves
1 tsp ground cumin
1/2 cinnamon stick
5 cloves garlic
1 onion
1 ½ Tbsp salt
32 oz beef broth 

Remove the seeds and veins from the chiles and simmer for 10 minutes.
Remove Chiles and add all of your ingredients except the meat to a blender to make the sauce. Add broth in there.
Season Beef cheeks with salt and some BBQ rub. Sear the meat for 90 seconds on each side then add to your Pressure Cooker. Pour the sauce all over and cook on charcoal or stove for an hour and half. Remove the meat from sauce. And pull the meat. You can use slow cooker but cook time will be about 4-5 hours.
Poor tortilla into a sauce and fry on vegetable oil, quickly add cheese, meat and some chopped red onion with fresh cilantro. Spicy level is medium. Enjoy.
